org.apache.mesos.config

Class ConfigNamespace

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.mesos.config.ConfigNamespace

  • public class ConfigNamespace
extends java.lang.Object
    A grouping of settings which all share a given namespace, which is defined as a prefix on the setting keys. Data is internally stored with the prefix(es) stripped out.

    • Method Detail

      • get

        public ConfigValue get(java.lang.String key)
        Returns a config value for the provided key within this namespace, with any prefix omitted, or null if a matching value could not be found. Use getAll() to see all values.
        Parameters:
        key - config key of the form "SOME_KEY" with any prefix omitted

      • getAll

        public <any> getAll()
        Returns an immutable copy of the full configuration within this namespace, with any prefixes omitted from keys.

      • updateEnvironment

        public CommandInfo updateEnvironment(CommandInfo command)
        Returns a new CommandInfo whose environment variables includes any values from this instance. Any matching entries already present in the provided CommandInfo will be overwritten.
